ack’s site-determined practice draws viewers’ focus to their connection to space and others sharing it. As Vazquez shows, Sandback’s art aims for nothing less than a total recalibration of the senses, as the spectator is caught on neither one side nor the other of an object or space, but powerfully within it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aConceptual art. 0aInstallations (Art). 0aMinimal sculpture. 0aSandback, Fred,-1943-2003. 0aSpace and time in art. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aFred Sandback.  aabsence.  aabstraction.  aconceptual art.  amateriality.  aminimalism.  apostminimalism.  asculpture.  aspace.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311071193640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226408064423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226408064/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles